Text.Value: The good constable may have had the wherewithal to stop us. It brings me great pleasure to speak of her in the past tense.
Sure thing - last time I got an invitation like this, life got a lot more interesting.
Look at you. An 'Avatar of Slaughter', indeed.
Another kill. Your technique is improving... Very novel, I must say.
Tell me what I must do.
Our gaze will remain upon you. You have great... potential.
Valeria was an incompetent... but having a celestial meddle in our affairs proved most disquieting.
It is good to meet somebody who recognises our talents - better still if they reward us for doing what comes naturally.
Don't you dare think of giving in. If you're so keen to hunt, we'll find deserving prey.
Sounds like random butchery. If I kill, it has to be with purpose.
Would you like to be more than a common murderer? To become an avatar of slaughter?
There you shall be judged. There you shall transcend.
Tear the hand from the corpse you have made in Bhaal's name.
Another life must be claimed in the name of our Lord. Choose wisely from this list.
Approach - unique. Form - sloppy. But the passion for killing - like a game. It's a shame I was the only acolyte here to witness you.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The doppelganger should have a maniac smile in his face.

Text.Value: Hang on - you're not seriously considering this, are you?
We will meet again, aspirant. Hopefully in the most auspicious of circumstance.
Turn around, and walk the other way.

EditorData.NodeContext: Flat warning - player has been approached by a creepy stranger asking if we want to become 'an avatar of slaughter'. Player asked stranger what they must do, but Jaheira butts in to respond bluntly.

Text.Value: This one's smile distresses Boo. If it is slaughter he wants, I will give it to him directly.
Such a penchant for violence... It makes me wonder.
Then enter Candulhallow's Tombstones. Announce your intention - to become an Unholy Assassin. A vessel for Lord Bhaal.
Chk - I know the thirst for blood. But you must kill with purpose, not for its own sake.
A most fitting demise for a most irksome thorn.
*The creature fixes you with an eerie gaze. It doesn't just see you, it sees through you.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The doppelganger look at the player and smiles with horrible, knowing malice.

Text.Value: Never.
I'd no idea you held such aspirations. Can't say I share them.
Unnatural wickedness. Take no part in this, please.
You must kill again - but I don't imagine that'll be a problem. End another target from this list.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: He gave us a copy of the target list of future victims.

Synopsis: Dialog that triggers when the players kill one person on the target list and they aren't part of the Bhaal Cult yet. Backup dialog if players kill the first doppelganger by mistake.
